1 Penguin Scatter plot weighted by Penguin Body Mass

library(readr)  # for read_csv
library(knitr)  # for kable
myfile <- "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datavizualization11/sta553/main/data/w02-penguins.csv"

Penguin <- read_csv(myfile)

#Refine scatter plot


#Importing image
library(jpeg)
library(RCurl)
penguin.img <- "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datavizualization11/sta553/main/Images/p.jpg"
my_pic <- readJPEG(getURLContent(penguin.img))
raster.penguin <- as.raster(my_pic) 

#Scatter Plot
plot(Penguin$bill_length_mm, Penguin$flipper_length_mm,
     xlab = "Bill length (millimeters)",
     ylab = "Flipper length (millimeters)",
     main = "Scatter Plot: Bill Length vs flipper length")
Bill.length = Penguin$bill_length_mm
Flipper.length = Penguin$flipper_length_mm
size.penguin = Penguin$body_mass_g/1800
species = Penguin$species

## color code
col.code = c(alpha("red",0.4),alpha("yellow",0.4),alpha("cyan",0.4))

## identifying the Species of Penguin
adelie.id = which(species=="Adelie")  # value are case sensitive!
chinstrap.id = which(species=="Chinstrap")
gentoo.id = which(species=="Gentoo")

## change the point size based on their body Mass
points(Bill.length[adelie.id], Flipper.length[adelie.id], pch = 19, col = col.code[1], cex = size.penguin)
points(Bill.length[chinstrap.id], Flipper.length[chinstrap.id], pch = 19,  col = col.code[2] , cex = size.penguin)
points(Bill.length[gentoo.id], Flipper.length[gentoo.id], pch = 19, col = col.code[3], cex = size.penguin)


legend("topleft", c("Adelie", "Chinstrap", "Gentoo"), 
                  col=c("red", "yellow", "cyan"),
                   pch=c(19, 19, 19), cex = .6)

#specify the position of the image through bottom-left and top-right coords
rasterImage(raster.penguin, 35,210,40,232)

text(52,179, "The size is proportional to Body Mass", col = "purple", cex = .5)

##Week 2

#Include Adelie penguins and Gentoo penguins from the Biscoe and Torgersen islands.
#Include only penguins with body_mass_g less than 5000 grams but more than 3500 grams.
Penguin1 <- subset(Penguin, (Penguin$species == ("Adelie") | Penguin$species == ("Gentoo")) & 
                     (body_mass_g>3500) & (body_mass_g<5000) &
                     (Penguin$island == ("Torgersen") | Penguin$island == ("Biscoe")))

drop_na(Penguin1)

# Rescale body_mass_g by dividing 4000 and rename it as BMI = body_mass_g / 4000.
newvar <- Penguin1 %>%
mutate(BMI = body_mass_g/4000)
head (newvar)
tail (newvar)

drop_na(Penguin1)
#Exclude variables X(observation ID), sex, year, and body_mass_g from the above subset.
pengdrop <- newvar[, -c(7:9)]
pengdrop <- pengdrop[, -1]
pengdrop
NA

#scatter plot

#Scatter Plot
plot(pengdrop$bill_length_mm, pengdrop$flipper_length_mm,
     xlab = "Bill length (millimeters)",
     ylab = "Flipper length (millimeters)",
     main = "Scatter Plot: Bill Length vs flipper length")
Bill.length = pengdrop$bill_length_mm
Flipper.length = pengdrop$flipper_length_mm
size.penguin = pengdrop$bmi*100
species = pengdrop$species

## color code
col.code = c(alpha("red",0.4),alpha("cyan",0.4))

## identifying the Species of Penguin
adelie.id = which(species=="Adelie")  # value are case sensitive!
gentoo.id = which(species=="Gentoo")

## change the point size based on their body Mass
points(Bill.length[adelie.id], Flipper.length[adelie.id], pch = 19, col = col.code[1], cex = size.penguin)
points(Bill.length[gentoo.id], Flipper.length[gentoo.id], pch = 19, col = col.code[2], cex = size.penguin)


legend("topleft", c("Adelie", "Gentoo"), 
                  col=c("red", "cyan"),
                   pch=c(19, 19), cex = .6)

#specify the position of the image through bottom-left and top-right coords
rasterImage(raster.penguin, 35,208,38,221)

text(45,181, "The size is proportional to BMI", col = "purple", cex = .5)
